   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In a charger a rectifier converts alternating current (AC) from
the rectifier mains to direct current (DC). The DC circuit supplies
the load and charges the battery bank. If the rectifier mains becomes
unavailable, the load is supplied without interruption by the battery
bank.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Optionally a charger can have:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
